name: AVPlayerItemAccessLogEvent
desc: A single entry in a player item's access log.

items.name: var uri: String?
items.desc: The URI of the playback item.

items.name: var serverAddress: String?
items.desc: The IP address of the server that was the source of the last delivered media segment.

items.name: var numberOfServerAddressChanges: Int
items.desc: A count of changes to the server address over the last uninterrupted period of playback.

items.name: var mediaRequestsWWAN: Int
items.desc: The number of network read requests over a WWAN.

items.name: var transferDuration: TimeInterval
items.desc: The accumulated duration, in seconds, of active network transfer of bytes.

items.name: var numberOfBytesTransferred: Int64
items.desc: The accumulated number of bytes transferred by the item.

items.name: var numberOfMediaRequests: Int
items.desc: The number of media read requests from the server to this client.

items.name: var playbackStartDate: Date?
items.desc: The date and time at which playback began for this event.

items.name: var playbackSessionID: String?
items.desc: A GUID that identifies the playback session.

items.name: var playbackStartOffset: TimeInterval
items.desc: The offset, in seconds, in the playlist where the last uninterrupted period of playback began.

items.name: var playbackType: String?
items.desc: The playback type.

items.name: var startupTime: TimeInterval
items.desc: The accumulated duration, in seconds, until the player item is ready to play.

items.name: var durationWatched: TimeInterval
items.desc: The accumulated duration, in seconds, of the media played.

items.name: var numberOfDroppedVideoFrames: Int
items.desc: The total number of dropped video frames

items.name: var numberOfStalls: Int
items.desc: The total number of playback stalls encountered.

items.name: var segmentsDownloadedDuration: TimeInterval
items.desc: The accumulated duration, in seconds, of the media segments downloaded.

items.name: var downloadOverdue: Int
items.desc: The total number of times that downloading the segments took too long.

items.name: var observedBitrateStandardDeviation: Double
items.desc: The standard deviation of the observed segment download bit rates.

items.name: var switchBitrate: Double
items.desc: The bandwidth value that causes a switch, up or down, in the item's quality being played.

items.name: var indicatedBitrate: Double
items.desc: The throughput, in bits per second, required to play the stream, as advertised by the server.

items.name: var observedBitrate: Double
items.desc: The empirical throughput, in bits per second, across all media downloaded.

items.name: var averageAudioBitrate: Double
items.desc: The audio track’s average bit rate, in bits per second.

items.name: var averageVideoBitrate: Double
items.desc: The video track’s average bit rate, in bits per second.

items.name: var indicatedAverageBitrate: Double
items.desc: The average throughput, in bits per second, required to play the stream, as advertised by the server.
